# DriftDetect API — HTTP request examples
# Run with JetBrains HTTP Client or VS Code REST Client

### Health check
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/
Accept: application/json

###

### ── DRIFT DETECTION ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── ###

### Detect drift (no persistence) — stable data, expect NO drift
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/detect
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reference": [
    [1.2, 3.4, 0.5], [0.9, 3.1, 0.6], [1.1, 3.3, 0.4], [1.3, 3.5, 0.7],
    [1.0, 3.2, 0.5], [0.8, 3.0, 0.6], [1.4, 3.6, 0.4], [1.2, 3.3, 0.5],
    [1.1, 3.1, 0.7], [0.9, 3.4, 0.5]
  ],
  "current": [
    [1.1, 3.3, 0.5], [1.0, 3.2, 0.6], [1.2, 3.4, 0.5], [0.8, 3.0, 0.6],
    [1.3, 3.5, 0.4], [1.1, 3.3, 0.7], [0.9, 3.1, 0.5], [1.2, 3.2, 0.4],
    [1.0, 3.4, 0.6], [1.1, 3.3, 0.5]
  ],
  "feature_names": ["age", "income", "score"],
  "strategy": "majority",
  "threshold": 0.05
}

###

### Detect drift (no persistence) — shifted data, expect DRIFT
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/detect
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reference": [
    [1.2, 3.4, 0.5], [0.9, 3.1, 0.6], [1.1, 3.3, 0.4], [1.3, 3.5, 0.7],
    [1.0, 3.2, 0.5], [0.8, 3.0, 0.6], [1.4, 3.6, 0.4], [1.2, 3.3, 0.5],
    [1.1, 3.1, 0.7], [0.9, 3.4, 0.5]
  ],
  "current": [
    [5.1, 8.3, 3.5], [4.9, 7.1, 3.6], [5.2, 8.4, 3.5], [4.8, 7.0, 3.6],
    [5.3, 8.5, 3.4], [5.1, 8.3, 3.7], [4.9, 7.1, 3.5], [5.2, 8.2, 3.4],
    [5.0, 8.4, 3.6], [5.1, 8.3, 3.5]
  ],
  "feature_names": ["age", "income", "score"],
  "strategy": "majority",
  "threshold": 0.05
}

###

### Create report + persist to DB (generates HTML) — unanimous strategy
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/report
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reference": [
    [25, 50000, 0.8], [30, 60000, 0.7], [35, 70000, 0.9], [28, 55000, 0.6],
    [32, 65000, 0.8], [27, 52000, 0.7], [31, 63000, 0.9], [29, 58000, 0.8],
    [33, 68000, 0.7], [26, 51000, 0.6]
  ],
  "current": [
    [45, 90000, 0.3], [50, 95000, 0.2], [55, 100000, 0.4], [48, 92000, 0.3],
    [52, 97000, 0.2], [47, 91000, 0.4], [51, 96000, 0.3], [49, 93000, 0.2],
    [53, 98000, 0.4], [46, 90500, 0.3]
  ],
  "feature_names": ["age", "salary", "engagement_score"],
  "strategy": "majority",
  "threshold": 0.05
}

###

### View HTML report in browser — replace {run_id} with ID from POST /report response
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/report/{{run_id}}/html
Accept: text/html

###

### ── METRICS & DASHBOARD ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── ###

### List all stored runs
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/metrics
Accept: application/json

###

### Aggregated detector performance
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/metrics/performance
Accept: application/json

###

### HTML dashboard (open in browser)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/metrics/dashboard
Accept: text/html

###

### Get single run metrics — replace {run_id} with a real ID
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/metrics/{{run_id}}
Accept: application/json

###